<function>

access:  static public

name: setFlash

param: string, $class

param: string, $key

param: mixed, $val

return: void

</function>

Sets a "read-once" session value for a class and key.

* Parameters:

 * string //$class//: The related class for the flash.

 * string //$key//: The specific type of information for the class.

 * mixed //$val//: The value for the key; previous values will be overwritten.

* Returns void

Sets a "read-once" session value for a class and key.

Taken from ideas popularized by Ruby on Rails, a "flash" is a session
value that propagates only until it is read, at which time it
is removed from the session.  This is useful for forwarding
information and messages between page loads.